Kaleb wrote:
&gt;
&gt; First, thank you so much for the response. That was a ton of help.
&gt; Just one more question. If I already have the jar files and want to
&gt; use my local copies, can I just add their location to the
&gt; project.properties, or do I also need to add them to the project.xml file?
&gt;




You need to add in both places.  Make sure that the ID in the 
project.xml dependency section matches the ID suffix in your 
&#39;maven.jar.ID&#39; entry in project.properties.
St.Ack


&gt;
&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, Michael Stack &lt;stack@...&gt; 
&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; See the dependencies section in the project.xml. If the xmlrpc lib is
&gt; &gt; available up in the maven1 ibiblio repository, maven should just fetch
&gt; &gt; it for you (You may need to add the following to your
&gt; project.properties
&gt; &gt; file because Heritrix is still stuck on maven 1.0.x:
&gt; &gt; maven.repo.remote=http://repo1.maven.org/maven 
&gt; &lt;http://repo1.maven.org/maven&gt;).
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Here is some more info on Heritrix and lib jars in case the above
&gt; proves
&gt; &gt; insufficent. Heritrix goes out of its way to defeat mavens dependency
&gt; &gt; fetching mechanism. It does this by setting &#39;maven.jar.override = on&#39;
&gt; &gt; in project.properties and then mapping project.xml dependency
&gt; &gt; references to actual locations under the lib directory (again in
&gt; &gt; project.properties). The thinking at the time was that the Heritrix
&gt; &gt; checkout contained all needed to run in the likes of eclipse. Maven
&gt; was
&gt; &gt; not required (This will probably change when we move to m2).
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; For example, for the libidn jar, in project.xml, it looks like this:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; ...
&gt; &gt; &lt;dependency&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;id&gt;libidn&lt;/id&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;version&gt;0.5.9&lt;/version&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;url&gt;http://www.gnu.org/software/libidn/ 
&gt; &lt;http://www.gnu.org/software/libidn/&gt;&lt;/url&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;properties&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;war.bundle&gt;true&lt;/war.bundle&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;ear.bundle&gt;true&lt;/ear.bundle&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;ear.bundle.dir&gt;APP-INF/lib&lt;/ear.bundle.dir&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;description&gt;GNU Libidn is an implementation of the
&gt; &gt; Stringprep,
&gt; &gt; Punycode and IDNA specifications defined by the IETF
&gt; &gt; Internationalized Domain Names (IDN) working group,
&gt; used for
&gt; &gt; internationalized domain names.
&gt; &gt; &lt;/description&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;license&gt;GNU Lesser General Public License
&gt; &gt; http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.txt 
&gt; &lt;http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.txt&gt;&lt;/license&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;/properties&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;/dependency&gt;
&gt; &gt; ...
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The &#39;id&#39; libidn from above is then mapped in project properties to the
&gt; &gt; libidn-0.5.9.jar with the following project.properties line:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; maven.jar.libidn = ${basedir}/lib/libidn-0.5.9.jar
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; You might also want to edit .classpath so your new jar shows in eclipse.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Hope this helps,
&gt; &gt; St.Ack
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Kaleb wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; I need to add the Apache XMLRPC jars to the Heritrix build, but I have
&gt; &gt; &gt; no idea how to add these to Maven. Could someone point me in the
&gt; &gt; &gt; right direction or at some pertinent documents? I&#39;ve had no problems
&gt; &gt; &gt; adding these libs to Netbeans projects, but I don&#39;t understand the
&gt; &gt; &gt; Maven documentation and am floundering.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Thanks,
&gt; &gt; &gt; Kaleb
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
